<TITLE> No compromise with dishonesty: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has warned civil servants that anyone caught stooping to dishonesty will lose their job, the health minister said on Sunday. AFM Ruhul Huq told reporters at the ministry Hasina expressed the desire to improve health services by evaluating the health policy. In a written statement, echoing the desire of the prime minister, the minister said, "To ensure health facilities for all, the health policy of the previous AL government will be re-evaluated in accordance with the demands of the time." The statement also said that 18,000 community clinics, of which 11,000 were built and incorporated in AL's previous health policy, will be in operation to ensure nutrition, child health and maternal wellbeing. To solve the arsenic problem, safe drinking water and sanitation will be ensured for all by 2011 and 2013 respectively, he added. On the policy for the posting of doctors, he said, "According to the policy, officials of the BCS health cadre will be given their first appointment in the rural areas for at least two years." He further said unless this mandatory period is served, a doctor will not be allowed to take any post-graduate course and will be unable to take leave to work abroad. The health minister expected the assistance of the media in developing the health system of the country, saying his door would be open 24 hours. bdne
